modules.description: Handles email composition and delivery through defined backends, supporting SMTP, SendGrid, and Mailgun. Operates on structured email data including sender, recipient, subject, and body. Enables seamless provider switching when sending transactional or notification emails.

provides a minimal interface for sending email via SMTP, mirroring the behavior of REST API counterparts. it includes no additional data types or operations beyond those defined in the underlying library. users can send emails using standard message structures and configuration settings. examples include sending a simple text message or attaching files through the provided interface.
